      <!-- Section 3 -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">How to Track Tiles During a Game</h2>

      <p>There are two main approaches to tile tracking, depending on your comfort level and the competitive setting:</p>

      <div class="grid gap-4 my-6">
        <div class="bg-purple-50 dark:bg-purple-900/20 border border-purple-200 dark:border-purple-700 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-300 mb-2">📝 Paper Tracking (Tournament Standard)</h3>
          <p class="text-sm">Write the full alphabet with counts before the game starts. Cross off letters as they're played. Most tournament players use a pre-printed tracking sheet with the distribution already listed — you simply mark each tile as it appears on the board.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-purple-50 dark:bg-purple-900/20 border border-purple-200 dark:border-purple-700 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-300 mb-2">🧠 Mental Tracking (Advanced)</h3>
          <p class="text-sm">Expert players track mentally by focusing on key tiles: the S tiles (4 total), blanks (2), and power tiles (Q, Z, X, J). You don't need to track every E — focus on tiles that change the game. Mental tracking requires practice but gives away nothing to your opponent.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-900/30 border border-green-200 dark:border-green-700 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-700 dark:text-green-300 mb-2">✅ Effective Approach: Priority Tracking</h3>
        <ol class="text-sm text-green-700 dark:text-green-200 space-y-1 list-decimal list-inside">
          <li>Track blanks first (2 in the set — game-changers)</li>
          <li>Track S tiles (4 total — plurals and hooks)</li>
          <li>Track power tiles: Q, Z, X, J (1 each)</li>
          <li>Track common bingo letters: E (12), A (9), I (9), R (6), N (6), T (6)</li>
          <li>Count remaining tiles in bag (100 minus board tiles minus both racks)</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <!-- Cross-link block -->
      <div class="bg-indigo-50 dark:bg-indigo-900/20 border border-indigo-200 dark:border-indigo-700 rounded-lg p-4 my-8">
        <p class="text-sm text-indigo-700 dark:text-indigo-300">📖 Want to understand how quickly tiles cycle through the game? Read our guide on <a href="/blog/tile-turnover-rate/" class="text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-400 underline font-medium">Tile Turnover Rate</a> for insights on game pacing and draw frequency.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 4 -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">What Tile Tracking Reveals</h2>

      <p>Once you're tracking tiles, the information you gain compounds as the game progresses:</p>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-6">
        <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-700 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400">60%</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">of the game — rough probability estimates</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-700 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400">80%</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">of the game — strong reads on opponent's rack</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-700 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400">90%</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">of the game — near-perfect deduction</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-700 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400">100%</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">bag empty — you know their exact tiles</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>Specifically, tracking reveals:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Bingo probability</strong> — if most high-frequency letters remain unseen, a bingo is likely coming</li>
        <li><strong>Danger tiles</strong> — if the Q hasn't appeared and few U tiles remain, your opponent may be stuck</li>
        <li><strong>Scoring potential</strong> — knowing whether power tiles are still out affects how aggressively you open the board</li>
        <li><strong>Defensive decisions</strong> — if both blanks are played, the threat of a bingo drops dramatically</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Section 5 -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">The Endgame: Perfect Information</h2>

      <p>Tile counting reaches its peak power in the endgame — the phase when the tile bag is empty. At this point, you can calculate your opponent's exact rack:</p>

      <div class="bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-900/20 border border-red-200 dark:border-red-700 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
        <p class="font-semibold text-red-700 dark:text-red-300 mb-2">🎯 The Endgame Formula</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-red-600 dark:text-red-200 font-mono">Opponent's tiles = 100 − (tiles on board) − (your rack tiles)</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-red-600 dark:text-red-200 mt-2">When the bag is empty, this gives you complete certainty about what your opponent holds.</p>
      </div>

      <p>With perfect information, you can:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Block their highest-scoring plays by denying premium square access</li>
        <li>Calculate whether to play off tiles or pass strategically</li>
        <li>Set up plays they cannot counter because you know their limitations</li>
        <li>Decide whether to go out first (ending the game and scoring their remaining tile values)</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Section 6 -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">When Tile Tracking Matters Most</h2>

      <p>While tracking from move one builds good habits, the critical window is the <strong>last 20-25 tiles</strong> in the bag. Here's why:</p>

      <div class="grid gap-3 my-6">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50 rounded-lg p-3">
          <span class="bg-amber-500 text-white text-xs font-bold rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">1</span>
          <p class="text-sm"><strong>Bag tile count drops below 7</strong> — no more full redraws are possible. Every draw is from a shrinking pool you can predict.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50 rounded-lg p-3">
          <span class="bg-amber-500 text-white text-xs font-bold rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">2</span>
          <p class="text-sm"><strong>S tiles and blanks are accounted for</strong> — you know whether hook plays and bingos are still threats.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50 rounded-lg p-3">
          <span class="bg-amber-500 text-white text-xs font-bold rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">3</span>
          <p class="text-sm"><strong>High-value tiles are scarce</strong> — if Z, X, or J haven't appeared, you can anticipate where they'll land.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50 rounded-lg p-3">
          <span class="bg-amber-500 text-white text-xs font-bold rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">4</span>
          <p class="text-sm"><strong>Point differentials tighten</strong> — a 15-point swing in the last 3 turns often decides the winner.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Cross-link block 2 -->
      <div class="bg-indigo-50 dark:bg-indigo-900/20 border border-indigo-200 dark:border-indigo-700 rounded-lg p-4 my-8">
        <p class="text-sm text-indigo-700 dark:text-indigo-300">🏁 Ready to master the final moves? Our <a href="/blog/endgame-strategy/" class="text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-400 underline font-medium">Endgame Strategy</a> guide builds on tile tracking to give you a complete framework for closing out games.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 pt-8 mt-12">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Related Articles</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
          <li><a href="/blog/tile-turnover-rate/" class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 hover:underline">Tile Turnover Rate — How Fast Tiles Cycle</a></li>
          <li><a href="/blog/endgame-strategy/" class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 hover:underline">Endgame Strategy — Winning the Final Moves</a></li>
          <li><a href="/blog/scrabble-tile-bag-distribution/" class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 hover:underline">Scrabble Tile Bag Distribution — Complete Breakdown</a></li>
        </ul>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-50 to-amber-100 dark:from-amber-900/30 dark:to-amber-800/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-700 rounded-xl p-6 text-center mt-10">
        <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-200 mb-2">Find your best words instantly</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-300 mb-4">Enter your rack and see every valid word scored and ranked — free, realtime, no signup.</p>
        <a href="/" class="inline-block bg-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-700 text-white font-medium px-6 py-2 rounded-lg transition-colors">Try the Word Finder →</a>
      </div>

